app.coinLeagues.theFirstThingYouNeedToSe: The first thing you need to setup is the Polygon network in your Metamask wallet, if you haven’t setup a MetaMask wallet click the button to add Polygon to your Metamask wallet
app.coinLeagues.useButtonsToAddMatic: Use the “Swap” “Buy Matic” or “Bridge” buttons to add Matic to your polygon wallet. Another easy way to send Matic to your Polygon wallet is to send Matic from an exchange that supports the polygon network. Withdraw Matic to your Polygon wallets address using the “POLYGON” network in the exchanges withdraw section. Once you have everything set up and connected in your Metamask wallet and you have MATIC in your Polygon network,
app.coinLeagues.clickTheCoinLeagueSectio: Click the Coin League section on the main menu to view the current games you can join.
app.coinLeagues.youWillSeeTheGamesInProg: You will see the games that are in progress. You can click and view any game happening.
app.coinLeagues.belowThatYouWillSeeGames: Below that you will see games that are available to play and that are waiting on players to start the game. When clicking on a game you will see the type of game it is either Bull or Bear. if it’s 1hr, 5 mins, 4hrs or even 24 hours.
app.coinLeagues.inTheFirstDropdown: In the first dropdown select your Captain Coin (the coin you think is going to gain the most for BULL games or lose the most for BEAR games) this captain coin will receive a 1.2x Multiplier on its % gain for bull games or % lost for bear games.
app.coinLeagues.inTheSecondDropdown: In the second dropdown select the remaining coins you want to play with up to 10 coins can be chosen depending on the game type. Once finished an “Enter Game” button will appear Press that and your Metamask wallet will prompt you to complete the transaction to enter the game. The captain coin with a 1.2x multiplier combined with your other coins will make up your team, their percentages will be added together to make up your total score.
app.coinLeagues.theGameWillNotStart: The game will not start until all players needed have entered.
app.coinLeagues.onceTheGameHasStarted: Once the game has started the countdown timer will start and begin calculating your rank based on the percentage gain or loss for the coins you chose.

app.dashboard.token.welcomeToTradingPage: Welcome to the Trading Page! This is where you can place market and limit orders for your favorite tokens across all supported Defi Protocols.
app.dashboard.token.hereYouCanCopyContra: Here you can copy the contract address for your selected token, share the URL on social media, and click the heart to add it to your favorites
app.dashboard.token.hereYouCanSeeTokenBa: Here you can see your token balance, buy with fiat, send and receive tokens.
app.dashboard.token.tradingSectionInfo: The Trading Section is where you can swap tokens and place limit orders. It also has a full-featured tradingview chart for decentralized protocols as well as a Binance chart.
app.dashboard.token.onThisTabYouCanSwap: On this tab you can swap tokens in the market section. Simply select your token pair and enter how many tokens you wish to buy or sell. Click trade, select the gas for your transaction, and click confirm!
app.dashboard.token.onTheLimitTabYouCanP: On the limit tab you can place limit orders without paying a gas fee to the Ethereum network. This only works by using Wrapped Ethereum (WETH) for the order. When your order price is reached, a wallet to wallet swap is performed with the taker paying the gas fee. If you don’t have WETH don’t sweat it! DEXKIT will convert your ETH for you . Once you have your WETH, simply enter the information for the trade, choose an expiry date, and click trade.
app.dashboard.token.onceYouHaveConfirmed: Once you have confirmed your limit order, it will show up in the “My Orders” tab. Here you will see all of your active limit orders that you have placed.
app.dashboard.token.tradeHistoryTabInfo: In "Trade History" tab you can see all of your buys and sells for a token and your calculated profit/loss. There are also links to the block explorer for the transaction.
app.dashboard.token.inThisTabYouCanSeeAn: In this tab you can see the analytics for your selected token including the market cap, trading volume, 24 hour high and low, as well as links to social platforms and web pages.
app.dashboard.wallet.walletPageInfo: The wallet page is where you can look at your total balances for your connected wallets across the Ethereum and Binance Smart Chain networks.
app.dashboard.wallet.youCanAlsoSeeDefi: You can also see any Defi assets that you are holding as well.
app.dashboard.wallet.assetChartInfo: The “Asset Chart” shows you your holdings over a period of time,
app.dashboard.wallet.transfersInfo: “Transfers” shows you all transfers of tokens in and out of your wallet.
app.dashboard.wallet.tradeHistoryInfo: “Trade History” shows buys and sells of tokens from your wallet. All assets can be filtered by network
app.dashboard.wallet.accounts.hereYouCan: Here you can add multiple accounts without the need to connect your Wallet.
app.dashboard.wallet.accounts.youreAbleT: You are able to switch accounts on the top menu right and the application it will auto update with selected account.
app.dashboard.wallet.accounts.firstAccou: The first account is the default. You can change clicking at the home button in other accounts.
app.dashboard.wallet.accounts.connectWal: Connect Wallet in case you need to interact with the network.
